      "text": "Problem Statement\n\nDesign a multi-region, multi-tenant job execution platform used by internal engineering teams to run infrastructure and data jobs (e.g., schema migrations, backfills, reindexing, batch analytics triggers).\n\nThe platform must support:\n        •        Exactly-once execution per job definition\n        •        Aggressive retries with fast recovery\n        •        Resource safety when jobs mutate shared infrastructure (databases, object stores, indexes)\n        •        Kubernetes-native execution\n        •        Cost controls to prevent runaway compute\n        •        Active/active multi-region operation\n\nThis is not a simple task queue. It is a platform capability used by dozens of teams with different reliability and cost profiles.\n\n⸻\n\nWhat You Are Designing\n\nYou are designing the job orchestration and execution control plane, not the business logic of the jobs themselves.\n\nYou may assume:\n        •        Jobs ultimately run as containers in Kubernetes\n        •        Teams submit jobs via an API\n        •        Jobs may have multiple stages\n        •        Jobs may require exclusive access to shared resources",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Problem Statement\n\nDesign a multi-region, multi-tenant job execution platform used by internal engineering teams to run infrastructure and data jobs (e.g., schema migrations, backfills, reindexing, batch analytics triggers).\n\nThe platform must support:\n        •        Exactly-once execution per job definition\n        •        Aggressive retries with fast recovery\n        •        Resource safety when jobs mutate shared infrastructure (databases, object stores, indexes)\n        •        Kubernetes-native execution\n        •        Cost controls to prevent runaway compute\n        •        Active/active multi-region operation\n\nThis is not a simple task queue. It is a platform capability used by dozens of teams with different reliability and cost profiles.\n\n⸻\n\nWhat You Are Designing\n\nYou are designing the job orchestration and execution control plane, not the business logic of the jobs themselves.\n\nYou may assume:\n        •        Jobs ultimately run as containers in Kubernetes\n        •        Teams submit jobs via an API\n        •        Jobs may have multiple stages\n        •        Jobs may require exclusive access to shared resources",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
